  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7105.79 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-6054.1M) and positive gamma at 7100 (+4823.3M), dealers are in a tricky spot where any move above 7115 forces them to sell into strength while moves below 7100 require buying the dip. The massive +7670.0M gamma wall at 7200 acts as a strong ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the 6873 flip level remains the critical downside inflection point. Given the PIN regime and current positioning just below negative gamma, expect dealers to provide modest support on any dips toward 7100 but face increasing headwinds on rallies toward 7150-7200.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect range-bound chop between 7100-7150 with upside capped near 7200.",
